---
import TerminalIcon from "../components/TerminalIcon.astro";
import PageShell from "../layouts/PageShell.astro";
---

<PageShell
	title="Testing and TDD Are Not Overkill"
	description="A short note on testing and engineering quality."
	canonicalUrl="https://overkill.dev"
>
	<script slot="search-engine-optimization-schema" type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "Person",
			"name": "Christian Rackerseder",
			"url": "https://www.echooff.dev",
			"sameAs": ["https://www.echooff.dev"]
		}
	</script>

	<div class="scanlines" aria-hidden="true"></div>
	<header class="hero frame">
		<TerminalIcon />
		<p class="kicker">SYSTEM BOOT: ENGINEERING OPINIONS.EXE</p>
		<h1>Testing is overkill.</h1>
		<p class="lede">Why test anything? Ship first. Think never. Hope forever.</p>
		<button class="button" id="evidence-button" type="button">Witness the evidence</button>
	</header>

	<main>
		<section class="reveal frame" aria-labelledby="plot-twist">
			<h2 id="plot-twist">Plot Twist</h2>
			<p>
				That opening line is satire. "Testing is overkill" is the fastest way to build brittle systems,
				panic-driven releases, and bug archeology as a full-time job.
			</p>
			<p>
				The real overkill is debugging production at 3:17 AM because we skipped ten minutes of design and ten
				lines of tests.
			</p>
			<p>Classic advice: "Why write tests when your commit message is descriptive?"</p>
		</section>

		<section aria-labelledby="myths-versus-reality-heading">
			<h2 id="myths-versus-reality-heading" class="visually-hidden">Myths versus reality</h2>
			<ul class="cards">
				<li>
					<article class="card frame">
						<h3>Myth: Tests slow delivery</h3>
						<p>Reality: rework slows delivery. Good tests are speed insurance with receipts.</p>
					</article>
				</li>
				<li>
					<article class="card frame">
						<h3>Myth: TDD is ceremony</h3>
						<p>Reality: tiny feedback loops are cheaper than giant post-release surprises.</p>
					</article>
				</li>
				<li>
					<article class="card frame">
						<h3>Myth: Quality is for perfectionists</h3>
						<p>Reality: quality is for teams that like sleeping during the night.</p>
					</article>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</main>

	<footer class="footer frame">
		<p>Need proof? Click the evidence button.</p>
		<p class="footer-note">Works on my machine. Production is another machine.</p>
	</footer>
	<script>
		import { registerEvidenceButton } from "../evidence/evidence-button.js";

		registerEvidenceButton({
			browserDocument: document,
			browserWindow: window
		});
	</script>
</PageShell>
